Table 1 shows our VMGP model outperforms all baselines on the four transform functions in the Latent Gaussian Environment. Looking qualitatively at the results, we see this performance arises directly from our modelâ€™s ability to learn non-Gaussian posteriors. We see that VMGP is the only method able to accurately represent this posterior as a multimodal mixture of point distributions: it learns that from the training data that the testing point is likely to either be âˆ’55-5, 00, or 555, rather than a sample from some Gaussian distribution like ALPaCA and DKT predict.
